<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-181-888  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 181 888.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  April 10 1989 n243 p52(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Financial networks: key tools of the 90's. (banking industry)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilde, Candee.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The fast-paced merger and acquisition rate in the banking industrymakes networking a key factor in gaining a competitive edge,forcing financial institutions to design versatile, cost-efficientnetworks capable of supporting future growth.andP;  For example, SouthCarolina National Corp recently converted its banking networkoperations from analog to digital, thereby reducing communicationscosts by $1.2 million and avoiding acquisition.andP;  In addition,banks aspiring to establish completely automated, full-servicebank branches must meet the demands of network security and accesscontrol.andP;  First Union National Bank plans to meet those demands byimplementing a satellite system that is expected to save the bank$3 million and 120 hours per workday over the next five years.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     BankingDeregulationInformation Resources ManagementNetworksAutomationGrowth.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>